### [Jeremiah Chapter 44](../../../bib/kjv/jer044.htm#001.md)

[Jeremiah](../../../bib/kjv/jer001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">jer 44:0</span></span>

Overview

[Jer 44:1](../../../bib/kjv/jer044.htm#001.md), Jeremiah expresses the
desolation of Judah for their idolatry; [Jer
44:11](../../../bib/kjv/jer044.htm#011.md), He prophesies their
destruction, who commit idolatry in Egypt; [Jer
44:15](../../../bib/kjv/jer044.htm#015.md), The obstinacy of the Jews; [Jer
44:20](../../../bib/kjv/jer044.htm#020.md), for which Jeremiah threatens
them; [Jer 44:29](../../../bib/kjv/jer044.htm#029.md), and for a sign
prophesies the destruction of Egypt.

